Enumerates every valid type/generic-arg append chain for Pass B's type-filling expansion, and substitutes the resulting rendered type text back into a chunk template at its type slot.

`fillings(opts: &TypeOptions) -> Vec<Filling>` is the main entry: for each `TypeDef` in `opts.types`, it emits one `Filling` per reachable append step — immediately terminal for arity-0 types, a chain of partial-then-terminal fillings built by `fill_args` for generic types, and a distinct free-type (`SKP`) filling that carries no rendered text at all (`text: String::new()`, `free_type: true`). `fill_args` recurses through `opts.generic_args` combinations, building up `args` and comparing `ar.len()` against `t.arity` via `u32::try_from(...).is_ok_and(...)` rather than a plain `==` — this guards against `arity` truncation/overflow rather than being purely stylistic. Each recursion step pushes a non-terminal `Filling` (rendered via `partial_type`, e.g. `"Map string"`) before going one level deeper, so the returned `Vec` contains every intermediate stroke-append point, not just complete types.

`render_type` substitutes `%t` markers in a `TypeDef.text` (e.g. `"Map<%t, %t>"`) with `args` positionally; a missing arg is silently rendered as an empty string rather than erroring — callers rely on this for partial fills. `partial_type` produces the bracketless form (`"Map"` or `"Map string"`) used for the non-terminal steps in a chain, derived from `type_name`, which strips at the first `<`.

`fill_template(template: &[Chunk], slot: usize, f: &Filling) -> Vec<Chunk>` applies one `Filling` to a template's single type-bearing chunk slot, branching on `f.free_type`. For free types it calls `with_free_type`, which does *not* insert literal text — it replaces the slot with a `Chunk::Landing(n)` where `n` is one greater than the maximum existing `Landing` number in the template, so a plain-profile expansion still lands on `%0` (typically the name slot) while a snippet-profile expansion gets its own tabstop at the type position. This depends on the `Landing` numbering convention used elsewhere in the chunk/template renderer — if that renderer assigns landing numbers differently, free-type tabstop ordering breaks. For non-free fillings, `with_types` swaps in `Chunk::Lit(f.text.clone())` at `slot` via `with_types(template, &[slot], ...)`, a general multi-slot substitution helper (pairs `slots` and `texts` by position, silently skipping any out-of-range index).

Depends on `TypeDef`/`TypeOptions` from `super::types` (expects fields `text`, `stroke`, `arity`, `free_type`, and `types`/`generic_args` collections) and `Chunk` from `crate::parse` (expects `Chunk::Lit` and `Chunk::Landing` variants); changes to either type's shape require updating this file's pattern matches.